         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the doing of ... [is] the cause. 3. Evil ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having (seen/heard?) precisely this one, the women of others ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... will be the fruit (of) giving ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... these five causes ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... comparable to ... . But whose ... will ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>35</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>100</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for sure he goes into suffering. 1. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the remembering through goodness ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I see which one (will) ... (in) that manner ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the remembering through (good)ness ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(the Buddha rank) without superior [and] perfect ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(As long as) ... (there will) not (be) any other thing ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Which living being through consciousness ... </seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>omäske(ṃ)</hi> may be the nominative/oblique singular or another case form.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment"><hi>räṣ</hi> is the end of an absolutive, maybe <hi>pälkoräṣ</hi> 'having seen' or <hi>kaklyuṣuräṣ</hi> 'having heard'.</note></p>
         </div>
